Package: anvltcc
Title: TinyCC Backend Bridge from 'anvl' Traces to 'tccquickr' Kernels
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Sounkou Mahamane", "Toure", , "sounkoutoure@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Compiles 'anvl' traced array programs to C kernels through
    'tccquickr' and the TinyCC just-in-time compiler from 'Rtinycc'.
    Traced graphs are lowered to declared R using anvl's own quickr
    lowering rules wherever those emit tccquickr's declared subset, with
    bridge-owned tinycc rules for primitives that have a native tccquickr
    surface form (matrix products as '%*%' contractions, aval-checked
    broadcast passthrough). The result is a millisecond-latency CPU
    compile path for anvl programs with no XLA dependency.
